#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
SConstruct for the standalone GDScript linter (homot-linter).

This is a BUILD MANIFEST documenting what's needed. The linter cannot be
built fully standalone because it depends on core/ types (Variant, String,
HashMap, etc.) which are tightly coupled to the engine.

PRACTICAL BUILD APPROACH:
    The linter is built as a second Program target within the engine's
    SCons build. Add the following to the root SConstruct after line
    `SConscript("platform/" + env["platform"] + "/SCsub")`:

        if env.get("linter", False):
            SConscript("linter/SCsub")

    Then build with:
        scons platform=windows target=editor dev_build=yes linter=yes

    This produces bin/homot-linter alongside the main engine binary.

FILES COMPILED (linter-specific):
    linter/main_linter.cpp              - CLI entry point
    linter/stubs/linterdb.cpp           - JSON data store
    linter/stubs/classdb_stub.cpp       - ClassDB stub + StubMethodBind
    linter/stubs/engine_stub.cpp        - Engine::has_singleton() stub
    linter/stubs/project_settings_stub.cpp - ProjectSettings stub
    linter/stubs/resource_loader_stub.cpp  - ResourceLoader stub
    linter/stubs/script_server_stub.cpp    - ScriptServer stub

LINKED AGAINST:
    All engine static libraries (core, scene, servers, modules, etc.)
    The stubs override real implementations at link time because stub
    .obj files are listed BEFORE the libraries in the link command.
"""
